WEBVTT

00:00.467 --> 00:02.667
<i>In New York City's war on crime</i>

00:02.668 --> 00:05.468
<i>the worst criminal
offenders are pursued</i>

00:05.568 --> 00:07.569
<i>by the detectives
of the Major Case Squad.</i>

00:07.537 --> 00:09.772
<i>These are their stories.</i>

00:17.245 --> 00:20.326
<i>Some souls
are lost forever</i>

00:20.394 --> 00:23.116
<i>Some hearts
won't e'er be found</i>

00:23.184 --> 00:26.394
<i>When a sailor
seeks a journey</i>

00:26.462 --> 00:29.514
<i>Never knowing
where it's bound</i>

00:29.582 --> 00:32.258
<i>The best things
he can offer</i>

00:32.325 --> 00:36.307
<i>Are a bowline
and a mast...</i>

00:36.375 --> 00:38.699
- It's Connolly's
and the bakery.

00:38.767 --> 00:41.529
<i>...And they're coming
awful fast</i>

00:41.597 --> 00:42.839
- Lovely.

00:42.907 --> 00:44.590
<i>We're a long, long way
from nowhere</i>

00:44.657 --> 00:46.874
<i>With a long,
long way to go</i>

00:46.942 --> 00:48.923
<i>Where these black tides</i>

00:48.991 --> 00:52.913
<i> have carried me before</i>

00:52.981 --> 00:54.588
<i>Delivered into darkness...</i>

00:54.656 --> 00:56.061
- Good morning, Mr. Dooley.
- Morning, boys.

00:58.812 --> 01:00.450
Morning, Marvin.

01:00.518 --> 01:04.101
- Hey, Jackie.
Just a sec.

01:04.169 --> 01:06.277
- Moira...

01:06.345 --> 01:08.253
As I live and breathe.

01:08.321 --> 01:10.629
- Hello, Mr. Dooley.

01:10.697 --> 01:13.242
- I need a hug.

01:17.561 --> 01:18.597
- I've missed you.

01:18.665 --> 01:20.739
- Oh, we missed you too.

01:20.807 --> 01:22.780
That old office
just isn't the same.

01:22.847 --> 01:25.024
- Well, I could come back.
I can still do afternoons.

01:25.092 --> 01:27.533
- No, no, no, it's all right.
It's all right, darling.

01:27.600 --> 01:29.341
I'm getting
her groceries today.

01:29.408 --> 01:30.579
- Oh, no, Mr. Dooley.

01:30.646 --> 01:32.420
- Thanks, Mr. Dooley.

01:32.487 --> 01:33.756
- Think nothing of it.

01:33.824 --> 01:36.999
You don't take care
of your own, who will, huh?

01:37.067 --> 01:40.208
- Hey, I-I called
your office yesterday.

01:40.275 --> 01:42.180
- Oh, yes.

01:42.248 --> 01:44.687
I meant to call you back.

01:44.755 --> 01:47.932
- I just thought
if you needed me for anything,

01:48.000 --> 01:49.902
I'm good now.

01:49.972 --> 01:53.714
I'm clean, I swear.

01:53.782 --> 01:57.625
- Well, that's
wonderful news, Edward.

01:57.693 --> 02:00.133
But you take care
of your mother.

02:00.201 --> 02:02.105
I've got my eye on you.

02:02.173 --> 02:04.644
- Thank you, Mr. Dooley.

02:07.920 --> 02:10.160
- Well, detective,

02:10.228 --> 02:11.930
what a pleasure it is
to see you

02:12.000 --> 02:15.007
taking the time to grace us
here in Broad Channel.

02:15.074 --> 02:16.743
- Listen to me.

02:16.811 --> 02:19.751
<i>We're a long, long way
from nowhere </i>

02:19.819 --> 02:22.591
<i>With a long,
long way to go</i>

02:22.658 --> 02:24.629
<i>Where these black tides</i>

02:24.697 --> 02:28.672
<i>have carried me before</i>

02:28.739 --> 02:30.209
- Who you taking down?

02:30.277 --> 02:31.745
- The russian.

02:31.813 --> 02:33.149
- Valeyev?

02:33.217 --> 02:34.686
I thought he was good people.

02:34.753 --> 02:36.356
- Not today.

02:36.424 --> 02:37.726
- You want a hand?

02:37.793 --> 02:39.663
- Nah, get some rest.

02:39.731 --> 02:42.804
<i>They say a wise man
falls for nothing </i>

02:42.871 --> 02:46.512
<i>But I haven't met one yet </i>

02:46.580 --> 02:49.017
<i>Boatloads full
of broken fools</i>

02:49.085 --> 02:51.523
<i>And the stumbles
they regret</i>

02:51.590 --> 02:54.763
<i>Oh, we're all just cuts
and bruises</i>

02:54.831 --> 02:58.003
<i>Yeah, we're only guts
and bones</i>

02:58.072 --> 03:00.543
<i>Busted hulls and gunwales</i>

03:00.611 --> 03:03.449
<i>Trying to find
our way back home </i>

03:03.516 --> 03:06.288
<i>We're a long, long way
from nowhere</i>

03:06.356 --> 03:09.594
<i>With a long,
long way to go</i>

03:09.662 --> 03:11.331
<i>Where these black tides</i>

03:11.399 --> 03:14.404
<i>Have carried me before</i>

03:16.809 --> 03:17.744
Get him, Jay.

03:20.417 --> 03:23.054
- You've got the right
to remain silent, sport.

03:23.122 --> 03:26.194
I suggest you use it.

03:26.262 --> 03:27.529
Nice guy, huh?

03:27.597 --> 03:29.099
What's your question?

03:29.167 --> 03:31.303
<i>We're a long, long way
from nowhere</i>

03:31.371 --> 03:34.809
<i>With a long,
long way to go</i>

03:34.877 --> 03:37.381
<i>Delivered into darkness</i>

03:37.449 --> 03:40.019
<i>To the center of the sin</i>

03:40.087 --> 03:43.057
<i>It's the middle
of nowhere</i>

03:43.126 --> 03:46.731
<i>And I'm going back again</i>

